<subSubSection id="20A5654A5173725D189EF9DBD590F892" pageId="16" pageNumber="53" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="680036C15173725D189EF9DBD590F892" blockId="16.[151,1437,1580,2037]" pageId="16" pageNumber="53">
<emphasis id="5ACBEAD35173725D189EF9DBD11DF997" bold="true" box="[151,273,1580,1605]" pageId="16" pageNumber="53">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
First and 2nd tarsomeres of male foreleg dorsodistally extended, with sex-combs: 1 
<taxonomicName id="AFBF4D425173725D1CCBF9DBD542F996" box="[1218,1358,1580,1604]" pageId="16" pageNumber="53" rank="subSpecies" subSpecies="tarsomere">st tarsomere</taxonomicName>
with a longitudinal row of 27–32 black, apically blunt teeth along entire length and a cluster of 7–11 black, apically sharp teeth distally; 2nd tarsomere with a distal cluster of 6–9 black, apically sharp teeth (
<figureCitation id="F0842A445173725D1C5EF983D4C0F95E" box="[1111,1228,1652,1677]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="17.[151,250,1860,1882]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,373,1839]" captionTargetId="figure@17.[151,1436,373,1839]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURE 8. Lordiphosa kimurai sp. nov. (A, B: paratype 06064; C−M: holotype 06065; N−P: paratype 06066). A, sexcombs on right foreleg (ventrolateral view); B, clusters of sex-comb teeth on distal extensions of 1st and 2nd tarsomeres (ventral view); C, D, periphallic organs (caudal and caudolateral view, respectively); E, epandrial ventral lobe (lateral view); F, surstyli and ventral spines of cercus (caudal view); G, inner surface of surstylus (caudolateral view); H, 10th sternite (ventral view); J̅K, phallic organs (ventral, ventrolateral, and lateral view, respectively); L, M, apical shape of paramere(s) and sensilla (ventral and ventrolateral view, respectively); N, O, oviscapt (ventral and lateral view, respectively); P, spermatheca." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1439537/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="53">Fig. 8A,B</figureCitation>
). Cercus ventrally tapered, elongated ventrad, with a fringe of 8–10 spines on apicoventral margin (
<figureCitation id="F0842A445173725D1C63F960D4D3F962" box="[1130,1247,1687,1712]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="17.[151,250,1860,1882]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,373,1839]" captionTargetId="figure@17.[151,1436,373,1839]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURE 8. Lordiphosa kimurai sp. nov. (A, B: paratype 06064; C−M: holotype 06065; N−P: paratype 06066). A, sexcombs on right foreleg (ventrolateral view); B, clusters of sex-comb teeth on distal extensions of 1st and 2nd tarsomeres (ventral view); C, D, periphallic organs (caudal and caudolateral view, respectively); E, epandrial ventral lobe (lateral view); F, surstyli and ventral spines of cercus (caudal view); G, inner surface of surstylus (caudolateral view); H, 10th sternite (ventral view); J̅K, phallic organs (ventral, ventrolateral, and lateral view, respectively); L, M, apical shape of paramere(s) and sensilla (ventral and ventrolateral view, respectively); N, O, oviscapt (ventral and lateral view, respectively); P, spermatheca." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1439537/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="53">Fig. 8C,F</figureCitation>
). Paramere flat, somewhat blade-shaped, only slightly curved ventrad, apically sharp and narrower than basal portion, subapically with 2 lateral sensilla and 1 acute, dorsal, somewhat membranous process bearing 1 sensillum at apex (
<figureCitation id="F0842A445173725D1D10F928D59CF92A" box="[1305,1424,1759,1784]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="17.[151,250,1860,1882]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,373,1839]" captionTargetId="figure@17.[151,1436,373,1839]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURE 8. Lordiphosa kimurai sp. nov. (A, B: paratype 06064; C−M: holotype 06065; N−P: paratype 06066). A, sexcombs on right foreleg (ventrolateral view); B, clusters of sex-comb teeth on distal extensions of 1st and 2nd tarsomeres (ventral view); C, D, periphallic organs (caudal and caudolateral view, respectively); E, epandrial ventral lobe (lateral view); F, surstyli and ventral spines of cercus (caudal view); G, inner surface of surstylus (caudolateral view); H, 10th sternite (ventral view); J̅K, phallic organs (ventral, ventrolateral, and lateral view, respectively); L, M, apical shape of paramere(s) and sensilla (ventral and ventrolateral view, respectively); N, O, oviscapt (ventral and lateral view, respectively); P, spermatheca." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1439537/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="53">
Fig. 
<date id="1C0110015173725D1D47F917D568F92A" box="[1358,1380,1760,1784]" pageId="16" pageNumber="53">8I</date>
–M
</figureCitation>
). Gonopods as long as aedeagus, somewhat narrow and dorsosubapically swollen in lateral view, without dorsoapical projection (
<figureCitation id="F0842A445173725D1996F8D0D1F4F892" box="[415,504,1831,1856]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="17.[151,250,1860,1882]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,373,1839]" captionTargetId="figure@17.[151,1436,373,1839]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURE 8. Lordiphosa kimurai sp. nov. (A, B: paratype 06064; C−M: holotype 06065; N−P: paratype 06066). A, sexcombs on right foreleg (ventrolateral view); B, clusters of sex-comb teeth on distal extensions of 1st and 2nd tarsomeres (ventral view); C, D, periphallic organs (caudal and caudolateral view, respectively); E, epandrial ventral lobe (lateral view); F, surstyli and ventral spines of cercus (caudal view); G, inner surface of surstylus (caudolateral view); H, 10th sternite (ventral view); J̅K, phallic organs (ventral, ventrolateral, and lateral view, respectively); L, M, apical shape of paramere(s) and sensilla (ventral and ventrolateral view, respectively); N, O, oviscapt (ventral and lateral view, respectively); P, spermatheca." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1439537/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="53">Fig. 8K</figureCitation>
). Spermathecal capsule not wrinkled horizontally, with apical indentation (
<figureCitation id="F0842A445173725D1D32F8D0D583F892" box="[1339,1423,1831,1856]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="17.[151,250,1860,1882]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,373,1839]" captionTargetId="figure@17.[151,1436,373,1839]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURE 8. Lordiphosa kimurai sp. nov. (A, B: paratype 06064; C−M: holotype 06065; N−P: paratype 06066). A, sexcombs on right foreleg (ventrolateral view); B, clusters of sex-comb teeth on distal extensions of 1st and 2nd tarsomeres (ventral view); C, D, periphallic organs (caudal and caudolateral view, respectively); E, epandrial ventral lobe (lateral view); F, surstyli and ventral spines of cercus (caudal view); G, inner surface of surstylus (caudolateral view); H, 10th sternite (ventral view); J̅K, phallic organs (ventral, ventrolateral, and lateral view, respectively); L, M, apical shape of paramere(s) and sensilla (ventral and ventrolateral view, respectively); N, O, oviscapt (ventral and lateral view, respectively); P, spermatheca." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1439537/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="53">Fig. 8P</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="20A5654A5173725F18CEF8BBD330FD22" lastPageId="18" lastPageNumber="55" pageId="16" pageNumber="53" type="description">
<paragraph id="680036C15173725C18CEF8BBD401FF07" blockId="16.[151,1437,1580,2037]" lastBlockId="17.[151,1436,151,320]" lastPageId="17" lastPageNumber="54" pageId="16" pageNumber="53">
<emphasis id="5ACBEAD35173725D18CEF8BBD15EF8B7" bold="true" box="[199,338,1868,1893]" pageId="16" pageNumber="53">Description</emphasis>
(characters commonly seen in 
<taxonomicName id="AFBF4D425173725D1AA5F8BAD338F8B6" authority="Katoh &amp; Zhang &amp; Toda &amp; Zhang &amp; Gao, 2018" authorityName="Katoh &amp; Zhang &amp; Toda &amp; Zhang &amp; Gao" authorityYear="2018" box="[684,820,1868,1892]" class="Insecta" family="Drosophilidae" genus="Lordiphosa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="53" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mikioides" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="5ACBEAD35173725D1AA5F8BAD2B7F8B6" box="[684,699,1869,1892]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="53">L</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="5ACBEAD35173725D1AC0F8BBD338F8B6" box="[713,820,1868,1892]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="53">mikioides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="41F857A85173725D1B32F8BBD398F8B7" box="[827,916,1868,1893]" pageId="16" pageNumber="53" rank="species">
<emphasis id="5ACBEAD35173725D1B32F8BBD398F8B7" bold="true" box="[827,916,1868,1893]" pageId="16" pageNumber="53">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
not repeated) (
<specimenCount id="7EB9FD485173725D1C34F8BBD458F8B6" box="[1085,1108,1868,1892]" pageId="16" pageNumber="53" type="male">♂</specimenCount>
, 
<specimenCount id="7EB9FD485173725D1C69F8BBD478F8B6" box="[1120,1140,1868,1892]" pageId="16" pageNumber="53" type="female">♀</specimenCount>
). Head (Pls 1F, 3–5F, 7F): Frontal vitta blackish brown. Fronto-orbital plate yellowish brown to dark brown, mediolaterally to anteriorly blackish brown. Ocellar triangle yellowish brown, marginally darker. Occiput dorsally yellowish brown, ventrally blackish brown. Postgena blackish brown, laterally paler, ventrally yellowish brown. Antennal pedicel brown to dark brown; 1 
<taxonomicName id="AFBF4D425173725D193AF82BD1D3F827" box="[307,479,2012,2037]" pageId="16" pageNumber="53" rank="subSpecies" subSpecies="flagellomere">st flagellomere</taxonomicName>
grayish yellow to dark gray; arista with short branches, 3–4 dorsal and 0–1 ventral, and minute terminal bifurcation. Supracervical setulae 19¯20 per side; postocular setae 18–20 per side. Clypeus pale brown. Cibarium with 28–29 medial and 16–18 posterior sensilla per side.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="680036C15172725C18CEFF28D304FE92" blockId="17.[151,1436,151,320]" pageId="17" pageNumber="54">Thorax (Pl. 1F) yellowish brown. Postpronotal lobe slightly darker on anterior margin. Mesonotum sometimes caudomedially darker. Scutellum medially somewhat grayish. Acrostichal setulae in ca. 6 irregular rows. Mid katepisternal seta indistinguishable from those below it.</paragraph>
<caption id="3CC066495172725C189EF8B3D53DF826" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1439537/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="54" startId="17.[151,250,1860,1882]" targetBox="[151,1436,373,1839]" targetPageId="17">
<paragraph id="680036C15172725C189EF8B3D53DF826" blockId="17.[151,1436,1860,2036]" pageId="17" pageNumber="54">
<emphasis id="5ACBEAD35172725C189EF8B3D542F889" bold="true" box="[151,1358,1860,1883]" pageId="17" pageNumber="54">
FIGURE 8. 
<taxonomicName id="AFBF4D425172725C1911F8B3D1E4F888" authority="Katoh &amp; Zhang &amp; Toda &amp; Zhang &amp; Gao, 2018" authorityName="Katoh &amp; Zhang &amp; Toda &amp; Zhang &amp; Gao" authorityYear="2018" box="[280,488,1860,1882]" class="Insecta" family="Drosophilidae" genus="Lordiphosa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="54" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kimurai" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="5ACBEAD35172725C1911F8B3D1E4F888" bold="true" box="[280,488,1860,1882]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="54">Lordiphosa kimurai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="41F857A85172725C19E7F8B2D232F888" box="[494,574,1861,1882]" pageId="17" pageNumber="54" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
(A, B: paratype #06064; C −M: holotype #06065; N −P: paratype #06066).
</emphasis>
A, sexcombs on right foreleg (ventrolateral view); B, clusters of sex-comb teeth on distal extensions of 1 
<taxonomicName id="AFBF4D425172725C1CB8F894D4F8F8AB" box="[1201,1268,1891,1913]" pageId="17" pageNumber="54" rank="subSpecies" subSpecies="and">st and</taxonomicName>
2nd tarsomeres (ventral view); C, D, periphallic organs (caudal and caudolateral view, respectively); E, epandrial ventral lobe (lateral view); F, surstyli and ventral spines of cercus (caudal view); G, inner surface of surstylus (caudolateral view); H, 10th sternite (ventral view); J̅K, phallic organs (ventral, ventrolateral, and lateral view, respectively); L, M, apical shape of paramere(s) and sensilla (ventral and ventrolateral view, respectively); N, O, oviscapt (ventral and lateral view, respectively); P, spermatheca.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="680036C15171725F18CEFF60D394FF07" blockId="18.[151,1437,151,1256]" pageId="18" pageNumber="55">Abdomen (Pl. 1F): Tergites nearly entirely black, somewhat glossy; tergite II laterally pale yellowish brown; female tergite VII yellowish brown, marginally dark brown to black.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="680036C15171725F18CEFF28D59CFE5A" blockId="18.[151,1437,151,1256]" pageId="18" pageNumber="55">
Male terminalia (
<figureCitation id="F0842A445171725F1985FF28D203FF2A" box="[396,527,223,248]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="17.[151,250,1860,1882]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,373,1839]" captionTargetId="figure@17.[151,1436,373,1839]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURE 8. Lordiphosa kimurai sp. nov. (A, B: paratype 06064; C−M: holotype 06065; N−P: paratype 06066). A, sexcombs on right foreleg (ventrolateral view); B, clusters of sex-comb teeth on distal extensions of 1st and 2nd tarsomeres (ventral view); C, D, periphallic organs (caudal and caudolateral view, respectively); E, epandrial ventral lobe (lateral view); F, surstyli and ventral spines of cercus (caudal view); G, inner surface of surstylus (caudolateral view); H, 10th sternite (ventral view); J̅K, phallic organs (ventral, ventrolateral, and lateral view, respectively); L, M, apical shape of paramere(s) and sensilla (ventral and ventrolateral view, respectively); N, O, oviscapt (ventral and lateral view, respectively); P, spermatheca." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1439537/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="55">Fig. 8C–M</figureCitation>
): Epandrium yellowish brown, nearly entirely pubescent, with ca. 17 long setae per side. Cercus yellowish brown, pubescent except for ventral elongation, with ca. 26 long setae. Surstylus with a row of ca. 17 prensisetae on caudal margin and ca. 53 recurved setae on ventral portion of inner surface. Tenth sternite pale brown, moderately sclerotized, broadly concaved dorsad, forming dome. Hypandrium triangular in ventral view. Aedeagus membranous except for apex and ventral margin, nearly entirely sheathed with gonopods.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="680036C15171725F18CEFE63D4FCFE27" blockId="18.[151,1437,151,1256]" pageId="18" pageNumber="55">
Female terminalia (
<figureCitation id="F0842A445171725F19A8FE63D216FE7E" box="[417,538,404,429]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="17.[151,250,1860,1882]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,373,1839]" captionTargetId="figure@17.[151,1436,373,1839]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURE 8. Lordiphosa kimurai sp. nov. (A, B: paratype 06064; C−M: holotype 06065; N−P: paratype 06066). A, sexcombs on right foreleg (ventrolateral view); B, clusters of sex-comb teeth on distal extensions of 1st and 2nd tarsomeres (ventral view); C, D, periphallic organs (caudal and caudolateral view, respectively); E, epandrial ventral lobe (lateral view); F, surstyli and ventral spines of cercus (caudal view); G, inner surface of surstylus (caudolateral view); H, 10th sternite (ventral view); J̅K, phallic organs (ventral, ventrolateral, and lateral view, respectively); L, M, apical shape of paramere(s) and sensilla (ventral and ventrolateral view, respectively); N, O, oviscapt (ventral and lateral view, respectively); P, spermatheca." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1439537/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="55">Fig. 8N–P</figureCitation>
): Tergite VIII yellowish brown. Epiproct and hypoproct grayish yellow. Sternite VII dark brown. Oviscapt valve apically with ca. 8 and 7̄9 ovisensilla on dorsal and ventral margins, respectively, laterally with ca. 83 minute ovisensilla. Spermathecal capsule introvert about 5/9 height of capsule.
</paragraph>
