<subSubSection id="20A5654A5171725F18CEFBC8D11EFB3A" pageId="18" pageNumber="55" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="680036C15171725F18CEFBC8D11EFB3A" blockId="18.[151,1437,151,1256]" pageId="18" pageNumber="55">
<emphasis id="5ACBEAD35171725F18CEFBC8D137FB8A" bold="true" box="[199,315,1087,1112]" pageId="18" pageNumber="55">Remarks.</emphasis>
This species closely resembles the foregoing new species, 
<taxonomicName id="AFBF4D425171725F1BF1FBB6D489FB8A" authority="Katoh &amp; Zhang &amp; Toda &amp; Zhang &amp; Gao, 2018" authorityName="Katoh &amp; Zhang &amp; Toda &amp; Zhang &amp; Gao" authorityYear="2018" box="[1016,1157,1088,1112]" class="Insecta" family="Drosophilidae" genus="Lordiphosa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="55" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mikioides" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="5ACBEAD35171725F1BF1FBB6D489FB8A" box="[1016,1157,1088,1112]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="55">L. mikioides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="41F857A85171725F1C98FBC8D4E2FB8A" box="[1169,1262,1087,1112]" pageId="18" pageNumber="55" rank="species">
<emphasis id="5ACBEAD35171725F1C98FBC8D4E2FB8A" bold="true" box="[1169,1262,1087,1112]" pageId="18" pageNumber="55">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
, in having the particular sex-combs and in the shape of terminalia, but can be distinguished from it by the arista with small branches and minute terminal bifurcation (nearly bare in 
<taxonomicName id="AFBF4D425171725F1B1AFB7ED390FB72" authorityName="Katoh &amp; Zhang &amp; Toda &amp; Zhang &amp; Gao" authorityYear="2018" box="[787,924,1160,1184]" class="Insecta" family="Drosophilidae" genus="Lordiphosa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="55" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mikioides">
<emphasis id="5ACBEAD35171725F1B1AFB7ED390FB72" box="[787,924,1160,1184]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="55">L. mikioides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), the gonopods dorsoapically without process (with sharp process in 
<taxonomicName id="AFBF4D425171725F1994FB5AD225FB16" authorityName="Katoh &amp; Zhang &amp; Toda &amp; Zhang &amp; Gao" authorityYear="2018" box="[413,553,1196,1220]" class="Insecta" family="Drosophilidae" genus="Lordiphosa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="55" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mikioides">
<emphasis id="5ACBEAD35171725F1994FB5AD225FB16" box="[413,553,1196,1220]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="55">L. mikioides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), and the spermathecal capsule apically indented (apically not indented in 
<taxonomicName id="AFBF4D425171725F1D8CFB5AD10EFB3A" authorityName="Katoh &amp; Zhang &amp; Toda &amp; Zhang &amp; Gao" authorityYear="2018" class="Insecta" family="Drosophilidae" genus="Lordiphosa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="55" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mikioides">
<emphasis id="5ACBEAD35171725F1D8CFB5AD10EFB3A" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="55">L. mikioides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
